{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"blunt-premedical-dairycow","creation_channel":"cli","description":"## What\nOne-time backfill: run the conservative blame -> commit -> ticket resolver over existing closed bugs to draw `caused_by` links retroactively, seeding source-of-bugs history.\n\n## Files\n- `scripts/backfill_caused_by.py` — new: iterate closed bugs, reuse `src/rebar/metrics/blame.py`, draw `caused_by` on high-confidence single culprits; `--dry-run` default.\n- `tests/unit/scripts/test_backfill_caused_by.py` — new.\n\n## Approach\nReuse the same conservative single-culprit resolver as the live auto-derivation (no new heuristic) so backfilled links are deterministic and consistent with going-forward ones. Idempotent (skips bugs already carrying a `caused_by`) and `--dry-run` by default so a run previews before writing; back-out is removing the additive links.\n\n## Tests\n- Unit (temp store + git): over a fixture of two closed bugs (one single-culprit, one ambiguous), the script proposes exactly one `caused_by` link; a second run is a no-op.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `tests/unit/scripts/test_backfill_caused_by.py` passes: the script links the single-culprit bug and skips the ambiguous one (`assert links == 1`).\n- [ ] re-running is idempotent — test asserts the second run draws 0 new links.","id":"2f8e-0f7e-6fea-4825","parent_id":"86ac-086a-20ad-4327","priority":2,"tags":["metrics","backfill"],"ticket_type":"task","title":"Backfill caused_by links over existing closed bugs (blame)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784416831364056001,"uuid":"926c87dd-5ece-4d69-a8ed-f4924344863e"}